DDeessccrriippttiioonn
       These  routines  return  the  wchar_t  character,  of type
       chtype, at the current position in the named  window.   If
       any attributes are set for that position, their values are
       OR-ed into  the  value  returned.   Constants  defined  in
       ocurses.h can be used with the & (logical AND) operator to
       extract the character or attributes alone.

   AAttttrriibbuutteess
       The following bit-masks  may  be  AND-ed  with  characters
       returned by winwch.

       Bit-mask   to   extract   character  Bit-mask  to  extract
       attributes Bit-mask to extract color-pair  field  informa-
       tion

